---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="How these are written"
	description="Every post here carries a badge saying how AI was involved. This is what that means and how I actually write them."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-07-17')}
	aiUsage="assisted"
>
	<p>
		Every post here has a small badge at the top saying how AI was involved:
		written by hand, dictated and transcribed, AI-assisted, or written by AI.
		It's one line of frontmatter on each post, so it can't drift from the truth.
	</p>

	<p>
		Most of what I publish is AI-assisted, and I don't want that word to be
		vague. Here's what it actually means for me.
	</p>

	<p>
		I keep a voice profile. It's a plain document of how I write: the words I use
		and the ones I won't, no em-dashes, a single word in CAPS when something
		needs the weight, short sentences where they earn it and longer ones where
		they don't, a real analogy when it helps and none when it doesn't. I didn't
		invent it. I read my own posts back and wrote down what was already there.
	</p>

	<p>
		For an assisted post, the AI drafts to that profile and then I edit every
		line. Not "read it and hit publish." I cut the parts that sound like a robot,
		fix the rhythm, kill any word I'd never say out loud, and rewrite anything
		that isn't true to what actually happened. If a sentence makes it in, it's
		because I'd have written it.
	</p>

	<p>
		The badge tells you how far that went. Written by hand means I typed every
		word myself. AI-assisted means I directed the piece and edited it, but AI
		helped draft. I'd rather just tell you than have you wonder.
	</p>

	<p>The robot helps. I still own every line.</p>
</Layout>
